original_title: Brooklyn: Ocean Parkway - Sea Breeze Avenue
text:
Ocean Parkway, west side, north of Sea Breeze Ave, showing the Church of the Guardian Angel (P.E).

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

original_title: Brooklyn: Ocean Parkway - Sea Breeze Avenue
text:
Ocean Parkway, west side, between Sea Breeze Ave., and the right of way of the B.M.T. Brighton Beach Line. To the left, partially seen, is the Hotel Shelburne.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

original_title: Brooklyn: Sea Breeze Avenue - Ocean Parkway
text:
(1) Sea Breeze Ave., at the N.W. corner of Ocean Parkway and Sea Breeze ave., showing the Hotel Shelburne, built by Edward Somerville. It was opened on June 15, 1904, and was known as the "Concourse Hotel" later it became the "Ricadonna" and after that the Jefferson. Louis Fisher bought it in 1913, and gave it the above name which remained until the building was dismantled and demolished in May 1928.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, showing the north side of the Hotel, viewed from the Brighton Beach subway station.

December 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing a view east to West 1st Street.

July 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

original_title: Brooklyn: Sea Breeze Avenue - Ocean Parkway
text:
Sea Breeze Ave., north side, between Ocean Pkwy., and Reigelmann Board Walk. In the foreground, is Sea Side Park. At left, the Peoples Bathing Pavilion.

August 8, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
